<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880715-0115 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business: First Fidelity Bancorp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FFB </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   FIRST FIDELITY BANCORP., Philadelphia, said it will redeem on Oct. 7 all 468,170 shares of its Series A convertible preferred stock for $25 a share. The banking company urged holders of the preferred to convert their stock to common before the redemption date. Each preferred share can be converted into 1.856 common shares. Based on the closing price of common July 7, holders who convert will receive common having a market value of about $75 for each preferred share, First Fidelity said. The right to convert the preferred will cease at the close of business Oct. 7. </TEXT></DOC>